In this letter, President Barack Obama informs Speaker Pelosi about the establishment of the National Commission on the BP Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill and Offshore Drilling. The purpose of this commission is to investigate the causes of the disaster and develop safety measures to prevent similar incidents in the future. The president requests Congress to consider an amendment to the FY 2010 proposals in the FY 2011 Budget to meet the urgent needs of the commission. The details of the request are provided in a letter from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.